    <p>The prototyping process is a series of small experiments in which the designer uses artifacts to elicit new information about users‚Äô as well as test key elements of their proposed solution. Both of my prototypes were designed to do both of those things, and ultimately succeeded by eliciting new insights about the industry and user experience, as well as validating and invalidating core value propositions.</p>
    <h3>Prototype #1: ‚ÄúCellar App‚Äù</h3>
    <h6>Hypothesis</h6>
    <p>Availability in proximity is the biggest factor in a wine purchase. Providing users a filterable stream of locally-available wines with relevant details solves for anxieties in the motivation and acquisition stages, creating a wine purchase.</p>
    <h6>Most Dangerous Assumptions</h6>
    <ul>
      <li>Wine buying is sufficiently painful for target users to hire help in the form of an app</li>
      <li>Users are open to shopping at proximate stores</li>
      <li>The tech can recommend wine better than the individual‚Äôs base intuition</li>
    </ul>
    <h6>User Groups</h6>
    <ul>
      <li>Tech-savvy wine consumers who know some things about their wine tastes but not enough to be carefree in their wine selection.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="cl-2">
        <h6>Testing For</h6>
        <ul>
          <li>Use-case viability</li>
          <li>Core USP: locally-available wine recommendations</li>
          <li>What wine profile information is relevant</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="cl-2">
        <h6>Not Testing For</h6>
        <ul>
          <li>Interface and information accuracy</li>
          <li>Personal list functionality</li>
          <li>Education</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <h6>Valid If</h6>
    <p>Users find a wine they are comfortable buying when provided personal criteria.</p>
    <h3>The Flow</h3>
    <p>A mobile application that presents the user with a filtered stream of locally-available (within an adjustable radius) wines paired with their CellarTracker.com rating and flavor abstracts.</p>
